=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Prepare the N-H fused methyl-isoxazole/lactam bicyclic core (intermediate A, the target scaffold without N-alkylation) by annulation/cyclization from the corresponding isoxazole/pyridyl lactam precursor. | Step 2: From 4-(aminomethyl)cyclopentanol, protect the amine as Boc and convert the alcohol into a leaving group (Br or OMs) to give electrophile B = 4-(Boc-aminomethyl)cyclopentyl bromide/mesylate. | Step 3: N-alkylate core A with electrophile B under base (e.g., Cs2CO3, DMF) to form the N-alkylated Boc intermediate C. | Step 4: Remove the Boc group with HCl/dioxane to afford the free aminomethyl cyclopentyl intermediate D. | Step 5: Install the final Cbz mask by treating D with benzyl chloroformate (CbzCl, base) to give the target Cc1onc2c1c(=O)n(C1CCCC(CNC(=O)OCc3ccccc3)C1)c1cnccc21.

